CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper April 27, 1957, pg. A3, reads: "YWCA Open House drew men and women from all parts of the city, Tuesday, from two until seven, to the Downtown 'Y.' Here Mrs. George L. West, president of the 'Y,' receives a handsome triangle of blue ribbons and flowers from Dolores Josephite, Cleo Simondinger and, right, Jane Poling. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Dolores Josephite, Cleo Simondinger, Mrs. George L. West, and Jane Poling holding triangle covered in bows and flowers, standing in Downtown YWCA with painting of mill scene in background
